Package com.sri.ai.util.functionalsequence

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FunctionalSequence<CoDomain>
    Intuitively, a functional sequence is the sequence formed by an (optional) initial arbitrary value, followed by the results of applying a function to a set of arguments, when these arguments are updated, one at a time.
    Refiner<T>
    A Refiner is meant to lazily compute successively better versions of something concurrently used by potentially many subscribers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractFunctionalRefiner<T,V>
    An abstract class implementing a Refiner based on a function, the arguments of which being provided by refiners as well.
    AbstractFunctionalSequence<T,V>
    An abstract class implementing basic functionality for a FunctionalSequence.
    AbstractRefiner<T>
    A basic abstract implementation of Refiner.
    IteratorRefiner<V>
    A refiner that merely goes over an iterator's range -- iterator MUST have at least one element in range.
    RefinerIterator<T>
    A Refiner wrapper providing it with an iterator interface.
  • Error Summary 
    Error Description
    AbstractFunctionalSequence.ArgumentWithNoValues
